Requirements:
To be considered for undergraduate admission to WUST, applicants must meet the following general requirements:

High School Diploma or GED

For international students, they must also meet the English Language Proficiency requirement.

A complete application package for undergraduate admission must include the following documents:

1. A completed and signed Application Form;
2. A non-refundable application fee of $100;
3. Official transcripts;
4. Evidence of High School graduation or GED;
5. English Proficiency test score report (for international students);
6. A financial support document (for international students).
